July 1 (Reuters) - Cryptocurrency exchange Coinbase Global Inc (COIN.O) said on Friday it was looking to expand in some European markets, even as the digital asset market continues to experience a downturn. The company is in the process of expanding in France, Italy, Spain and the Netherlands, it said in a blog post, adding that it was aiming to launch its retail, institutional and developer products in all those markets. (https://bit.ly/3ugNHoa) In June, Coinbase slashed 1,100 jobs, constituting nearly 18% of its workforce.  read more  Our Standards: The Thomson Reuters Trust Principles.